## Test Anti-Pattern Audit — `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

**10 tests reviewed. 10 of 10 have critical issues.**

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test suite. Every public method on `ProductCatalog` is called (achieving high line coverage), but almost nothing is actually verified. A bug in any method would likely *not* cause a test failure.

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| Critical | 7 |
| High     | 1 |
| Medium   | 2 |

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic — entire file)

All 10 tests methodically call every public method with zero or trivial assertions. The suite exists to inflate coverage, not to catch bugs.

| Test Method | Lines | Problem |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` | 19-21 | **No assertion at all.** Calls `AddProduct` but never checks the product was saved. |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` | 33-36 | **No assertion at all.** Updates price but never verifies the new price took effect. |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` | 39-43 | **No assertion at all.** Removes a product but never verifies it's gone. |
| `GetProductCount_Works` | 63-66 | **No assertion at all.** Gets count, discards the result. |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` | 69-74 | **No assertion at all.** Applies 10% discount but never checks that prices changed. |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` | 85-88 | **No assertion at all.** Imports CSV but never checks products were created. |
| `GetProduct_Works` | 24-29 | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — confirms the product *exists* but never verifies its SKU, name, or price are correct. A `GetProduct` that returns a completely wrong product would pass. |
| `SearchProducts_Works` | 46-52 | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — never checks the list contains the right product or has the expected count. A `Search` returning empty list still passes (empty list ≠ null). |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` | 55-60 | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — same issue. |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` | 77-82 | `Assert.IsNotNull` only — never validates CSV content. An `ExportToCsv` that returns `"garbage"` would pass. |

**Concrete fixes** (representative examples):

```csharp
// BEFORE — AddProduct_Works (line 17)
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProduct()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var retrieved = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
